OL,3,CDisused coal tips safety bill becomes
OL,4,Claw in Wales
OL,6,FCurrently, the Mining Remediation
OL,7,FAuthority (formerly the Coal
OL,8,FAuthority) inspects them once and
OL,9,Ftwice a year respectively.
OL,11,FThe UK Government pledged #118m over
OL,12,Fthree years in the recent Spending
OL,13,FReview towards coal tip safety.
OL,15,FThe Welsh Government says its own
OL,16,Fcontribution of more than #100m means
OL,17,Fmore than #220m has been invested in
OL,18,Ftackling the problem.
